observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management to require the Municipal Accountant to:

Conduct regular monitoring of receivable accounts to ensure that these are collected when these become due and demandable;

Take responsibility to conduct a final review, analysis and reconciliation of all dormant accounts pursuant to the guidelines and procedures in reconciling and cleaning the books of accounts of LGUs of dormant receivable accounts for fair presentation in the Financial Statements provided by COA Circular No. 2016-005.

We recommended that the Management:
ensure the optimal utilization of the 20% DF by implementing the PPAs to help achieve the desirable socio-economic targets and developmental outcomes of the LGU for the benefit of its constituents;
identify those fully completed PPAs with unutilized balances and PPAs that could no longer be implemented, and reprogram the same to other social, economic, developmental or environmental PPAs.

We recommended Management to require the Municipal Accountant to:

Conduct regular monitoring of receivable accounts to ensure that these are collected when these become due and demandable;


Take responsibility to conduct a final review, analysis and reconciliation of all dormant accounts pursuant to the guidelines and procedures in reconciling and cleaning the books of accounts of LGUs of dormant receivable accounts for fair presentation in the Financial Statements provided by COA Circular No. 2016-005.

We recommended that Management instruct the Municipal Accountant to:


a.	Make the necessary adjustments on misclassified accounts amounting to ₱308,535.30 to arrive at the correct balances of the affected accounts and;


b.	Strictly comply with the timely withholding of taxes and effect the adjusting entries to recognize the withholding taxes portion of Accounts Payable.

We recommended and Management agreed to the following courses of action:

Provide enough storage space wherein unserviceable properties could be properly secured and safeguarded against the elements and instruct all offices to surrender their reported unserviceable properties in preparation for their ultimate disposal;

Direct the GSO Designate to finalize the Inspection and Inventory Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) as basis in recording the dropping from the books the unserviceable properties carried in the PPE accounts; 

Direct the Appraisal and Disposal Committee to evaluate the reasonable appraisal value of the unserviceable properties listed in the IIRUP and promptly cause the disposal of these properties; and



Advise the concerned personnel to submit the IIRUP to the Accounting Office upon completion of the disposal activity as it will be the basis for adjusting the balances of the affected PPE accounts.

